.TH "ata_eh_set_lpm" 9 "ata_eh_set_lpm" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
ata_eh_set_lpm \- configure SATA interface power management
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" ata_eh_set_lpm
.BI "(struct ata_link *link "  ","
.BI "enum ata_lpm_policy policy "  ","
.BI "struct ata_device **r_failed_dev "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "link" 12
link to configure power management
.IP "policy" 12
the link power management policy
.IP "r_failed_dev" 12
out parameter for failed device

Enable SATA Interface power management.  This will enable
Device Interface Power Management (DIPM) for min_power and
medium_power_with_dipm policies, and then call driver specific
callbacks for enabling Host Initiated Power management.

LOCKING:
EH context.
.SH "RETURN"
0 on success, -errno on failure.
